ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: 1.  Did the participant receive vagus nerve stimulation during the index episode?
2. Did the participant receive an ECT during the index episode?
3.  Did the  participant receive rTMS during the index episode?
4.  Has the participant experienced  any other somatic treatments during the index episode?
5.  Is the participant receiving psychotherapy that is depression-specific (CBT or IPT)?
6.  Is the participant currently enrolled in another research study that contraindicates participation in the EMBARC study?
7.  Does the participant have any history of adequate treatment (dose and duration) with poor response to either Sertraline (SERT) or Bupropion (BUP)?
8.  Does the participant have any history of poor tolerance to Sertraline (SERT) or Bupropion (BUP) treatment?
9.  Has the participant taken fluoxetine in the past 6 weeks?
10.  Has the participant taken benzodiazepine in the past 4 days?
11.  Has the participant taken any other antidepressants other than those listed above in the last 3 weeks?
Date field of first suicide attempt

Notes: 1=Absent; 2=Thoughts of dying but no thoughts of suicide; 3=Occasional thoughts of suicide but no plans; 4=Often thought about suicide or has thought of a specific method; 5=Had a plan or made a gesture; 6=Made preparation for a potentially serious suicide attempt; 7=Suicide attempt with definite intent to die or be potentially medically harmful

ElementDescription: Subject related information (e.g the affection, phenotype, disease information, etc.).
Study; The code for each individual study
